p: Finally, beans incubated with A. obtectus, which were previously treated with different doses of C. winterianus, showed weight losses ranging between 0.83 ± 0.31% (120 μL dose) and 2.01 ± 0.38% (6 μL dose), while beans under the control treatment (2.44 ± 0.64%) had weight loss significantly higher (F = 2.77; df = 5.18; p = 0.050) than the rest of doses evaluated ( Figure 4).
